SIMPLE: whither
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whither
<hw>Whith"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>whider</ets>. AS. <ets>hwider</ets>; akin to E. <ets>where</ets>,
<ets>who</ets>; cf. Goth. <ets>hvadr⟦emac⟧</ets> whither. See
<er>Who</er>, and cf. <er>Hither</er>, <er>Thither</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To what place; -- used interrogatively; <as>as,
<ex>whither</ex> goest thou?</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Whider</xex> may I
flee?⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sir Valentine, <qex>whither</qex> away so fast?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To what or which place; -- used
relatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That no man should know . . . <qex>whither</qex> that he went.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We came unto the land <qex>whither</qex> thou sentest us.</q>
<rj><qau>Num. xiii. 27.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To what point, degree, end, conclusion, or design;
whereunto; whereto; -- used in a sense not physical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor have I . . . <qex>whither</qex> to appeal.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Any whither</b></col>, <cd>to any place; anywhere.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Any whither</xex>, in hope of life
eternal.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Jer. Taylor.</au> -- <col><b>No whither</b></col>,
<cd>to no place; nowhere.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>2 Kings v.
25.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Where.</syn> <usage> -- <er>Whither</er>,
<er>Where</er>. <xex>Whither</xex> properly implies motion to place, and
<xex>where</xex> rest in a place. <xex>Whither</xex> is now, however, to
a great extent, obsolete, except in poetry, or in compositions of a
grave and serious character and in language where precision is required.
<xex>Where</xex> has taken its place, as in the question,
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Where</xex> are you going?⟦rdquo⟧</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1650 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whithersoever</ent>⟦br⟧
